I"s<h1 id="zinc-purification">Zinc Purification</h1>
<p>Used food grade equipment: mason jars…<br />
<strong>Zinc</strong> - 65.38 g/mol</p>
<p><strong>Zinc Carbonate</strong> - 125.388 g/mol - ZnCO<sub>3</sub></p>
<p><strong>Zinc Sulfate</strong> - 161.436 g/mol - ZnSO<sub>4</sub></p>
<p><strong>Zinc Acetate</strong> - Zn(O2CCH3)2 - 183.48 g/mol</p>
<p><strong>Sodium Carbonate</strong> - 105.99 g/mol</p>
<h2 id="procedure">Procedure</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y3WJFsr7HDY">Make Zinc Metal by Electrolysis - Nurdrage</a> 1. Added 50g ZnSo4 to 200 ml H2O 2. Stirred until dissolved 3. Added ~0.1g zinc metal 4. Stirred for 30 min 5. Allowed to settle; decanted; filtered 6. Electroplated zinc metal onto aluminum cathode, MMO on titanium anode; constant stirring; 5v; 7. Recovered 7.61g solid zinc metal; rinsed, dried; recovered sulfuric acid; 8. Added 300 ml household vinegar 9.</p>
<ol type="1">
<li>Zinc sulfate made previously by reacting impure zinc with sulfuric acid, filtering, then evaporating to dryness.</li>
<li>50.0 g zinc sulfate</li>
<li>57.7 g/100 ml solubility in H<sub>2</sub>O @ 25 &amp;deg C; 101g/100ml H<sub>2</sub>O at 70 &amp;deg C</li>
<li>added 100 ml dH<sub>2</sub>O</li>
<li>add extra 25 ml dH<sub>2</sub>O</li>
<li>filtered</li>
<li>rinsed with dH<sub>2</sub>O</li>
<li>add 0.15g powdered zinc metal</li>
<li>stir for 5 min</li>
<li>filtered</li>
<li>let sit 48 hrs</li>
<li>2x filter (small white precipitate formed)</li>
<li>recrystallized- evaporated until first crystals formed then cooled in freezer</li>
<li>33g sodium carbonate dissolved in 100ml H<sub>2</sub>O, filtered</li>
<li>Added to sulfate soln. until pH 7 - overshot adjusted with dilute HCl</li>
<li>evaporated to dryness; yield: 38g ZnCO<sub>3</sub> hydrate</li>
<li>neutralized with household vinegar (slowly)</li>
<li>filtered; a surprising amount of white precipitate left over - common ion solubility problems?</li>
<li>evaporated to dryness; &lt;100 °C to preserve hydrate form</li>
<li><strong>FAILED</strong> - sodium acetate present and discolors product from #19 -&gt; need to find an alterate route without sodium ion</li>
</ol>
